      "type": "feature",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>Once per respite, Gragnir can commune with any tree, root, or wooden structure that has been alive within the last decade. He asks one question. The answer arrives as sensation — warmth, cold, weight, movement — never words. He interprets. The Director may give him one piece of true lore they could not have known otherwise.</p>",
          "director": "<p>Director note: Information from trees is always true but often cryptic or symbolic. A dying tree in the courtyard knows something heavy walked past. A burned stump remembers heat but not faces. Use this sparingly to deliver lore the party couldn't access otherwise, or to confirm what they already suspect.</p>"
        },
        "source": {
          "book": "Svellheim Campaign (Era of Embers)",
          "page": "Beat 03",
          "license": ""
        },
        "_dsid": "speaks-to-trees",
        "advancements": {},
        "prerequisites": {
          "value": "",
          "dsid": [],
          "level": null
        }
      },
      "_id": "7q7KMLKNLwKmdIK3"
    },
    {
      "name": "Through the Cracks",
      "img": "icons/magic/fire/flame-burning-campfire-grey.webp",
      "effects": [],
      "flags": {},
      "folder": null,
      "sort": 0,
      "ownership": {
